# Copy this file to .env (which is gitignored) and fill in real values.
# Do NOT commit .env.
#
# The defaults below are written for the personal edition (single user,
# single machine). You can run the desk with NO env vars at all — the
# entries here only enable optional integrations or change behavior.

# ── Single-user / LAN access ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Single-user mode on localhost — skips the device-token pairing gate.
# Set to 1 if this is your own machine and you don't want to pair every
# browser to a token.
# HOLON_OPEN_DEMO=1

# Recommended when accessing the desk from a phone on the same Wi-Fi.
# Treats private-LAN IPs (10.x / 192.168.x / 172.16-31.x / 100.x Tailscale)
# as "the local desktop" so the Windows browser can read the pairing code
# and the phone can pair.
# HOLON_LAN_ACCESS=1

# ── Secretary warm-process tuning (optional) ──────────────────────────────
# Override the default Haiku model + low effort. Most owners shouldn't
# need to touch these.
# HOLON_SECRETARY_MODEL=claude-haiku-4-5
# HOLON_SECRETARY_EFFORT=low

# ── OAuth integrations (deferred) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# NextAuth was removed in feat/remove-nextauth (Task #12) — this app is a
# local single-user desk, no sign-in. Standalone OAuth flows for Gmail /
# Calendar / Drive will return per-connector when needed.

# Token encryption-at-rest key. Kept around because @holon/core's
# token-storage substrate validates it at boot when present (see
# packages/core/src/token-storage-adapter.ts). Generate via:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
# HOLON_TOKEN_ENC_KEY=

# Shared secret guarding the legacy plugin sidecar's token-fetch / refresh
# routes. Only needed if you wire up the Hermes-plugin pattern — most users
# never will. Generate via: openssl rand -base64 32
# HOLON_PLUGIN_SHARED_SECRET=

# ── Storage paths (optional overrides) ────────────────────────────────────
# Default: ~/.holon/owner.sqlite (key-value store).
# HOLON_DB_PATH=/custom/path/owner.sqlite

# ── Bug-report → GitHub issue (optional, maintainer-only) ─────────────────
# When set, /api/v1/admin/bugs files an issue in the named repo. Skip for
# personal edition. Token must be a fine-grained PAT scoped to Issues
# (read+write) on the specific repo.
# HOLON_FEEDBACK_GITHUB_TOKEN=github_pat_...
# HOLON_FEEDBACK_GITHUB_REPO=your-org/your-repo

# ── Telegram ingress (optional) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to 'false' in secondary worktrees if two instances share a bot token
# (avoids Bot API 409 conflict storm).
# TELEGRAM_INGRESS_ENABLED=false

# ── Mobile build (used by scripts/build-android-apk.sh, NOT desk runtime) ─
# URL the mobile bundle calls; baked at build time.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DESK_ORIGIN=http://your-desk-ip:3110
